Reasoning: The paper discusses network coded algebraic gossip, which is a communication protocol used in computer networks. This falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses queuing approaches and worst-case guarantees, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and theoretical computer science (cs.DS). Lastly, the paper mentions round robin routing, which is a scheduling algorithm used in operating systems and computer networks, and thus falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SI).
